The Italian Cultural Institute in Cairo, an office of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and International Cooperation, promotes and disseminates the knowledge of the Italian language and culture in Egypt. It organizes a wide range of cultural events in collaboration with Egyptian cultural institutions and in synergy with the Sistema Paese; it responds to requests for information on Italian culture and the Italian university system; it organizes Italian language and culture courses and maintains regular contact with all Egyptian universities where Italian language and culture are taught.

The Italian Cultural Institute in Cairo serves as the coordinator of the Italian Cultural Institutes in the Middle Eastern and Sub-Saharan area through the exchange of projects and the organization of joint cultural events. The Italian Cultural Institute in Cairo offers the Egyptian public the following services:

Italian language and civilization courses taught by native-speaking and/or qualified teachers for teaching Italian as a second language (L2);

Lending and consultation of over 36,000 volumes in Italian at the “Giuseppe Ungaretti” Library, available to course students and subscribers;

Information and documentation on Italy in the cultural and academic fields;

Information on the granting of scholarships;

Information on universities in Italy.

For concerts, certain art exhibitions, and major events, the Institute collaborates with Egyptian cultural institutions: the Ministry of Culture, the Ministry of Education, the Ministry of Higher Education, the Supreme Council of Antiquities, the Supreme Council of Culture, the Cairo Opera House, the Sayed Darwish Theater in Alexandria, the Bibliotheca Alexandrina, the Egyptian Museum and the National Museum of Egyptian Civilization in Cairo, the Must University in Cairo, the National Museum and the Greco-Roman Museum of Alexandria.

